# &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;User Manual
#### To do list app

Version 0.1 

20th October 2019




**_System Overview:_**

The to do list is an application that allows user to simplify user’s task management which can help them to list down the tasks, to get organized and get things done.
This application allows users to use a text-based user interface via the command-line. With this application the user should be able to create new tasks and assign them a title, due date, project and status. The user should also be able to edit the task, mark the status as done or remove tasks. They can also view all the tasks or can view the collection of tasks sorted by date or project. They can also quit and save the current task list to file, and then restart the application with the former state restored. 	


**System configuration:**

Each user uses their own workstation running any operating system. On those workstations the user needs to execute the to do list application program. User can perform any list of activities using this application as show below



**Using the application:**

User will have following functionalities while using the todolist app:

1.Show Task
 
Choosing option 1 will enable user to view all his tasks he has addded in the todolist application. 

2.Add a Task:

On choosing the option 2 user will be able to add a task in the application. User needs to enter four fields as shown belows

	•	Title
	•	Due Date 
	•	Project 
	•	Status

3.Delete Task

On choosing option3 user will be able to delete all his tasks he has logged in the application. 

4.Edit/Update Task:
  
On choosing option 4 user will be able to update the task in the application. 

5.Save and quit Task:

On choosing option 5 user will be able to save all his tasks he has logged in the application.User will also be able to quit from the application